value.value: The recruitment of hematopoietic stem cells from the bone marrow into peripheral blood.
A substance that is added to a system or compound to improve its characteristics.

label.value: Regimen Used to Treat Plasma Cell Myeloma

value.value: Any regimen that can be used for the treatment of plasma cell myeloma.
A regimen consisting of melphalan and prednisone used as induction treatment for plasma cell myeloma.
A regimen consisting of vincristine, doxorubicin and dexamethasone used as induction treatment for plasma cell myeloma.
A regimen consisting of thalidomide and dexamethasone used for the treatment for plasma cell myeloma.

The hydrochloride salt of a synthetic piperidine ester with opioid analgesic activity. Meperidine mimics the actions of endogenous neuropeptides via opioid receptors such as the mu-opioid receptor, thereby producing characteristic morphine-like effects including analgesia, euphoria, sedation, respiratory depression, miosis, bradycardia and physical dependence.

label.value: Testicular Mixed Embryonal Carcinoma and Seminoma

value.value: A malignant mixed germ cell tumor arising from the testis.  It is characterized by the presence of a mixture of embryonal carcinoma and a seminomatous component.
A regimen consisting of liposomal doxorubicin, vincristine and dexamethasone used as induction therapy for plasma cell myeloma.
A regimen consisting of dexamethasone, thalidomide (DT) and cisplatin, doxorubicin, cyclophosphamide and etoposide (PACE) used for the treatment of relapsed and refractory plasma cell myeloma.

label.value: Regimen Used to Treat Pancreatic Carcinoma

value.value: Any regimen that can be used for the treatment of pancreatic carcinoma.
A regimen consisting of gemcitabine and erlotinib used for the treatment of pancreatic cancer.
A sample of blood collected from a newborn child that is utilized to screen for both disorders present at birth and subsequent disease development.
This gene is involved in a variety of important cellular processes, such as cell division.

Human KIF4A wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of Xq13.1 and is approximately 131 kb in length. This allele, which encodes chromosome-associated kinesin KIF4A protein, is involved in the regulation of microtubule directionality and subsequent cellular movement.

A measure of joint flexibility consisting of flexion, how far it can bend, and extension, how far it can stretch. It is usually measured by the number of degrees from the starting position of a segment to its position at the end of its arc.
Chromosome-associated kinesin KIF4A protein (1232 aa, ~140 kDa) is encoded by the human KIF4A gene. This protein plays a role in mitosis, and is thought to play a role in tumor formation.
A measure of how far a patient can move a body part against gravity

label.value: Testicular Mixed Embryonal Carcinoma and Teratoma

value.value: A malignant mixed germ cell tumor arising from the testis, characterized by the presence of an embryonal carcinomatous component and a teratomatous component.
Any regimen that can be used for the treatment of sarcoma.
A regimen consisting of doxorubicin, ifosfamide, dacarbazine and mesna used to treat unresectable soft tissue sarcoma.
A measure of how far a joint can move when it is being manipulated by someone other than the patient.
Of or related to the hands; reference to a task or activity being done by hand (as opposed as being performed with the assistance of automation or other supportive means).
This gene may play a role in tumor suppression.
A regimen consisting of doxorubicin, ifosfamide and mesna used for the treatment of unresectable soft tissue sarcoma.
A regimen consisting of doxorubicin and dacarbazine used for the treatment of unresectable soft tissue sarcoma.

Human FLCN wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 17p11.2 and is approximately 25 kb in length. This allele, which encodes folliculin protein may play a role in tumor suppression, but an exact function has yet to be identified. Mutations or aberrations in the gene result in Birt-Hogg-Dube syndrome.

Folliculin protein (579 aa, ~64 kDa) is encoded by the human FLCN gene. This protein is purported to play a role in tumor suppresion, but an exact function has yet to be identified. Mutations and truncations in the protein have been implicated in the pathogenesis of fibrofolliculoma formation, Birt-Hogg-Dube syndrome, and colorectal tumorigenesis.

label.value: Testicular Mixed Embryonal Carcinoma and Teratoma with Seminoma

value.value: A malignant mixed germ cell tumor arising from the testis.  It is characterized by the presence of a mixture of embryonal carcinoma, a teratomatous component, and a seminomatous component.
A regimen consisting of cisplatin, doxorubicin and paclitaxel used for the treatment of advanced stage or recurrent endometrial cancer.
To freeze rapidly so as to preserve structure and prevent ice crystal formation.

label.value: Regimen Used to Treat Malignant Ovarian Neoplasm

A solution of water soluble glycols and resins that provide a specimen support matrix for cryostat sectioning at temperatures of -10 degrees C and below.
Any regimen that can be used for the treatment of melanoma.
A regimen consisting of cisplatin, vinblastine and dacarbazine used for the treatment of advanced-stage or metastatic malignant melanoma.
This gene is involved in DNA double-strand break repair.

Human BRIP1 wild-type allele is located within 17q22-q24 and is approximately 180 kb in length. This allele, which encodes fanconi anemia group J protein, is involved in the repair of double-strand DNA breaks and is critical for genomic integrity. The allele may be a target of germline cancer-inducing mutations. If the gene is mutated in persons who have Fanconi Anemia, there may be an enhanced risk for the development of breast cancer. As a result, the gene is often identified as a breast cancer susceptibility gene.

Fanconi anemia group J protein (1249 aa, ~141 kDa) is encoded by the human BRIP1 gene. This protein is involved in DNA-dependent ATPase activity, 5' to 3' DNA helicase activity, and homologous recombination.
This gene plays a role in tumor suppression.
An immature teratoma that arises from the testis.

Human NPRL2 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 3p21.31 and is approximately 4 kb in length. This allele, which encodes GATOR complex protein NPRL2, plays a role in growth suppression and may be involved in tumor suppression for multiple cancers.
GATOR complex protein NPRL2 (380 aa, ~44 kDa) is encoded by the human NPRL2 gene. This protein plays a role in the regulation of signaling.
A lymphoma that arises from the kidney. There is no evidence of a systemic lymphoproliferative disorder.
A diffuse large B-cell lymphoma that affects the kidney.
An imaginary surface formed by extension of a point through any axis or two definite points; any flat two-dimensional surface.
A class which hold the roles which are assumed by a particular group in the context of a protection group.
A detailed examination, analysis, or critical inspection of a subject designed to discover facts about it.
One or more series of images taken on a single visit to a medical facility.
